sndlib.core.model
Class Model

java.lang.Object
  sndlib.core.model.Model

public final class Model
extends java.lang.Object

This class represents the model component of a network design problem.
It consists of several submodels describing whether the links are directed or undirected, whether the capacities are modular or linear, whether an explicit list of admissible paths should be taken into account or not, etc.
Instances of this class are immutable, that means that a Model cannot be changed after construction. For this reason a ModelData object is needed to construct a Model instance.

Author:
Roman Klaehne
See Also:
ModelData, Problem
